[50.143576, "o", "PRD written to `docs/helix/01-frame/prd.md`. It covers the three features (F1: `--to-celsius`, F2: `--to-fahrenheit`, F3: formatted output), technical constraints, and non-goals — kept short for a demo project.\r\n"]
[50.143737, "o", "── docs/helix/01-frame/prd.md ──\r\n"]
[50.144853, "o", "# PRD: hello-helix\r\n\r\n## Overview\r\n\r\n**hello-helix** is a Node.js CLI tool that converts temperatures between Fahrenheit and Celsius.\r\n\r\n## Goals\r\n\r\n- Provide a simple, correct temperature conversion CLI\r\n- Output results formatted to one decimal place\r\n- Minimal dependencies; easy to install and use\r\n\r\n## Features\r\n"]
[50.14489, "o", "\r\n### F1: Convert Fahrenheit to Celsius\r\n\r\n**Command:** `convert --to-celsius <temp>`\r\n\r\nConverts the given Fahrenheit temperature to Celsius using the formula:\r\n`C = (F - 32) × 5/9`\r\n"]
[50.145182, "o", "...\r\n\r\n"]
[52.146353, "o", "\r\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\r\n  Step 2: Create a user story\r\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\r\n\r\n"]
[77.895799, "o", "Created `docs/helix/01-frame/user-stories/US-001-temperature-conversion.md` with two acceptance criteria covering both conversion directions, referencing PRD features F1, F2, and F3.\r\n"]
[77.89585, "o", "── docs/helix/01-frame/user-stories/US-001-temperature-conversion.md ──\r\n"]
[77.89732, "o", "# US-001: Temperature Conversion\r\n\r\n**As a** user,\r\n**I want to** convert temperatures between Fahrenheit and Celsius via the CLI,\r\n**so that** I can quickly get accurate conversions from the command line.\r\n\r\n## References\r\n\r\n- PRD Features: F1, F2, F3\r\n\r\n## Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\n### AC-1: Fahrenheit to Celsius"]
[77.897479, "o", "\r\n\r\n**Given** the user runs `convert --to-celsius 212`\r\n**Then** stdout contains `100.0`\r\n\r\n### AC-2: Celsius to Fahrenheit\r\n\r\n**Given** the user runs `convert --to-fahrenheit 0`\r\n"]
[77.897778, "o", "...\r\n\r\n"]
[79.899643, "o", "\r\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\r\n  Step 3: Create a technical design\r\n"]
[79.899712, "o", "━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\r\n\r\n"]
[121.511163, "o", "Technical design created at `docs/helix/02-design/technical-designs/TD-001-temperature-conversion.md`. It covers:\r\n\r\n- **Single file** `bin/convert.js` serving as both CLI entry point and importable module\r\n- **Two exported functions**: `toFahrenheit(c)` and `toCelsius(f)` — pure functions, easy to test\r\n- **CLI parsing** via `process.argv` with `--to-celsius` and `--to-fahrenheit` flags, no dependencies\r\n- **Entry point guard** using `require.main === module`\r\n- **Output format**: `<input>°<unit> = <result>°<unit>` with `toFixed(1)`\r\n- **Traceability** back to both acceptance criteria from US-001\r\n"]
[121.511339, "o", "── docs/helix/02-design/technical-designs/TD-001-temperature-conversion.md ──\r\n"]
[121.512614, "o", "# TD-001: Temperature Conversion\r\n\r\n## References\r\n\r\n- PRD Features: F1, F2, F3\r\n- User Story: US-001\r\n\r\n## Overview\r\n\r\n"]
[121.512645, "o", "A single Node.js module (`bin/convert.js`) that converts temperatures between Fahrenheit and Celsius via CLI flags. The module also exports pure conversion functions for testing.\r\n\r\n## Module Design\r\n\r\n### File: `bin/convert.js`\r\n\r\n**Exports:**\r\n\r\n| Function | Signature | Description |\r\n|---|---|---|\r\n"]
[121.51273, "o", "| `toFahrenheit` | `(c: number) => number` | Converts Celsius to Fahrenheit: `C × 9/5 + 32` |\r\n"]
[121.512914, "o", "...\r\n\r\n"]
[123.51424, "o", "\r\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\r\n  Step 4: Create failing tests (Red phase)\r\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\r\n\r\n"]
[148.072902, "o", "── tests/convert.test.js ──\r\n"]
[148.073946, "o", "const { describe, it } = require('node:test');\r\nconst assert = require('node:assert');\r\nconst { toFahrenheit, toCelsius } = require('../bin/convert.js');\r\n\r\ndescribe('toFahrenheit', () => {\r\n  it('converts 0°C to 32.0°F', () => {\r\n    assert.strictEqual(toFahrenheit(0), 32.0);\r\n  });\r\n});\r\n\r\ndescribe('toCelsius', () => {\r\n"]
[148.073976, "o", "  it('converts 212°F to 100.0°C', () => {\r\n    assert.strictEqual(toCelsius(212), 100.0);\r\n  });\r\n\r\n  it('converts 98.6°F to approximately 37.0°C', () => {\r\n    const result = toCelsius(98.6);\r\n    assert.ok(Math.abs(result - 37.0) < 0.1, `Expected ~37.0 but got ${result}`);\r\n  });\r\n});\r\n"]
[148.074222, "o", "...\r\n\r\n"]
