[197.582316, "o", "\r\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\r\n  ACT 4: Critical Review\r\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\r\n\r\n"]
[230.185414, "o", "## Review Findings\r\n\r\n### Spec-to-Implementation Alignment\r\n\r\n- **AC-1 and AC-2 are covered.** `toCelsius(212) → 100.0` and `toFahrenheit(0) → 32.0` are both tested and the implementation is correct.\r\n- **Formulas are correct** in both code and docs: `(F-32)*5/9` and `C*9/5+32`.\r\n- **Output format matches spec.** `<input>°<unit> = <result>°<unit>` with `toFixed(1)`.\r\n- **Entry point detection** uses `require.main === module` as designed.\r\n- **Error handling** matches TD-001: missing flag, missing value, and NaN all print usage to stderr and exit 1.\r\n\r\n### Errors / Issues\r\n\r\n- **PRD says entry point is `bin/convert`** (no extension), but the actual file is `bin/convert.js`. There is no extensionless `bin/convert` shim or `package.json` `\"bin\"` field pointing to it — so `npx convert` or a global install wouldn't work as the PRD implies.\r\n\r\n### Omissions\r\n\r\n- **No CLI integration tests.** TD-001 traceability table promises \"CLI integration test\" for both AC-1 and AC-2, but `tests/convert.test.js` only has unit tests on the exported functions. No test spawns the process and checks stdout output format.\r\n- **No error-path tests.** TD-001 specifies error behavior (missing flag → stderr + exit 1, NaN value → stderr + exit 1). These are untested.\r\n- **No negative / edge-case tests.** Negative temperatures, zero Celsius-to-Fahrenheit, and fractional inputs are unexercised (only the 98.6 approximate test touches decimals).\r\n- **US-001 acceptance criteria are thin.** They only check that stdout \"contains\" a number — they don't verify the full output format (`<input>°F = <result>°C`). A regression could break formatting while still passing ACs.\r\n\r\n### Mischaracterizations / Minor Issues\r\n\r\n- **TD-001 export table column mismatch.** The `toFahrenheit` description says `C × 9/5 + 32` but labels the formula variable as `C` while the signature column says `(c: number)` — this is fine but inconsistent with the `toCelsius` row which uses uppercase `F` in the formula but lowercase `f` in the signature. Cosmetic only.\r\n- **PRD non-goals list \"Units beyond Fahrenheit and Celsius\"** but doesn't mention Kelvin explicitly — fine for now but could be more precise if scope questions arise.\r\n\r\n### Summary\r\n\r\nThe implementation is **correct and matches the specs** for the happy path. The main gaps are: (1) missing CLI integration tests that TD-001 explicitly promises, (2) no error-path test coverage, and (3) a `bin` entry-point mismatch between PRD and the actual file.\r\n"]
[232.187117, "o", "\r\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\r\n  ACT 5: Queue Health & Triage\r\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\r\n\r\n"]
[252.117948, "o", "Analyzing gaps between specs and implementation...\r\n\r\nGaps found:\r\n  - Test plan specifies 3 cases but error paths are untested\r\n  - No CLI integration tests for acceptance criteria\r\n  - Missing package.json bin field for global install\r\n\r\n"]
